metadata.name: Tezumie #409
metadata.description:
Tezumie are interdimensional beings who seemingly spawn out of thin air. Tezumie are obsessed with Eating, fighting, and Collecting junk they find throughout the universe. Once a Token is minted, you will spawn your very own Tezumie! 

Beware, there is more to them than they let on. They are not Restricted to the blockchain, and you may notice strange things appearing and disappearing around you. You have been warned.

metadata.description:
All of us have dreams, and everyone would like to meet a fairy, a genie, a wizard, or someone else who will make our dreams come true in a snap of a finger or with the wave of a wand. But we're the only ones who can do it. We are those magical unicorns, unique, inimitable, with our own qualities and magical abilities.
These unicorns are the visualization of our inner selves that makes our dreams come true. An embodiment of all the best with a huge positive magical power.

metadata.name: SINGULARITY #135
metadata.description:
A random generated gravitational singularity travels through the void.
Objects behave in several ways. Many have satellites, some even have two.

Each singularity occurs in different space.
Some are colorful, some are minimal. 
Beware of the solar winds. They can mess things.
A tiny part of singularity will end up in a solar storm.

Good luck!

Coded in Amsterdam with Javascript & Hydra.

metadata.name: Stripped Down V3 #110
metadata.description:
The last series in the journey of geometric shapes.
This was the initial algorithm behind "Zometric" and "Delight". Starting with the basic grid, rectangles and parallel lines. I used the black color for the composition with a pastel palette for the background. hope you enjoy it.

metadata.name: BlockonBlock #109
metadata.description:
‘BlockonBlock’ is the precursor and reserve pass for the upcoming ‘Hashway ‘69 Revisited’ collection by pixelwank. 
Free mint for pixelwank holders on tezos - After 3 days any remainders will be opened up to the public for 2tez.  

‘BlockonBlock’ was a study of rectangles following on from the use of circles in Generacci. 
Placements & building sizes are based on numbers from the fibonacci sequence. 

I had a blast making these and I hope they bring the collector as much enjoyment.

'Hashway '69 Revisited' coming soon :)

23 colour palettes 
14 colour overlays 
21% chance of extra lines
Click the image or press ‘s’ or ‘S’ in live move to save a 3000x3000 png 

Thanks for collectin’ & shoutouts to Circolors for the support <3 

R.I.F.F. 
Remember it’s for fun

metadata.name: Summerland #240
metadata.description:
A random summer mountain landscape based on the technical core of 'Winterland'.
Varies in wind-strength, skycolor, depth and more.
Day/Night cycle based on your local system-time. 
Click/Tap for day/night change.

In Live-Mode...
...press 'r' to toggle responsive/fullscreen mode
...press 's' to save current frame
...click/tap/press space for day/night change

-@TeNinEightNFTs

Created with p5.js using map2.
